children.subject:
188 is a really cool course to take, but I definitely wouldn't expect it too have much bearing on SWE post-graduation. It's also one of the easier upper division courses.

I can't comment too much on 164, but I'd imagine it being a lot more useful for SWE than 188.

If you've only taken two techs at most so far, I wouldn't take all 3.

history.content:
I'm thinking of graduating this fall, taking 161 with either 188 or 164. It seems that 164 is much more useful for SWE but 188 sounds interesting. I'm not particularly serious about AI/ML, nor have any experience in it. Should I take 188 for the sake of taking an AI course at Cal? I'm taking 162 and really like the class; I've heard that 164 has a similar "tone" as 162.

Is taking all three too much? For all my previous semesters, I've taken only two techs at most per semester.
history.subject: 161 with 188 or 164
